            <section class="grid-2-2">
                <h3>An award-winning Design System</h3>
                <div>
                    <p>
                        As a consultant, your stay on a company is always on a time limit, and by the Summer of 2017,
                        Ericsson decided to start building up their in-house design team, to better prepare for a more
                        design driven future.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        By the end of the year, the <b>Ericsson Design System</b> that grew from my team's experience
                        creating the tech stack agnostic <b>Loki</b> CSS/JS framework and the UX vision work we did for
                        the new brand, was awarded a <a href="https://www.ericsson.com/en/press-releases/2018/8/ericsson-wins-red-dot-awards-for-brand-and-interface-design"
                            target="_blank" rel="noopener">Red Dot Design Award</a> and an <a
                            href="https://ifworlddesignguide.com/entry/256283-ericsson-design-system" target="_blank"
                            rel="noopener">IF Design Award</a>.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        In the years after, the work we did was the foundation from which a team of 6 people with 4
                        consultants, grew to a multifunctional research, design, and engineering team with over
                        30 people (2 short of the total count of designers in the company during my tenure) that 
                        are trusted to prototype and kickstart the most innovative initiatives at Ericsson.
                    </p>
                </div>
